<p>Lt Gen Vladimir Alekseyev, described as a deputy director/deputy head of Russia’s military intelligence service (the GRU), was shot several times in the stairwell of his apartment building in northwestern Moscow on Friday and taken to hospital. Reports described his condition as serious or critical. Russian investigators said an unidentified gunman opened fire and fled, and authorities are investigating the shooting. The attack comes as Russia’s war in Ukraine continues, and follows other incidents Russia has blamed on Ukraine. Russian officials alleged Ukrainian involvement, while Ukraine made no immediate public comment in the reporting cited.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/d03zNtPtxNoutViI2AUMw452k_dH89sywaOONyE_f4OQUyc1t7t6Ys16j65rUsTd8AP-O3RGtv1c04wcNuS1nLYOQTowW9oJB8sQg8t6PSuN' alt='Law enforcement officers and journalists work outside a residential building where the assassination attempt on Lt Gen Vladimir Alekseyev took place in Moscow on February 6, 2026.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Sanctions history: Alekseyev has faced U.S. sanctions, including over alleged cyber interference in the 2016 U.S. presidential election, and EU sanctions over the 2018 poisoning of Sergei Skripal and his daughter in Salisbury, England.</li><li>Profile details: Dawn reported Alekseyev is 64, was born in Ukraine when it was part of the Soviet Union, and has received the “Hero of Russia” award, one of the country’s top state honors.</li><li>Pattern of attacks: Russian investigators and state-linked outlets described the shooting as the latest in a string of assassination attempts that Russian authorities have blamed on Ukraine since the full-scale war began in 2022.</li><li>Role in war: The New York Times reported Alekseyev was among the officials who supplied intelligence to the Kremlin ahead of Russia’s invasion of Ukraine, making him a prominent figure in Russia’s wartime security apparatus.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Sergei Lavrov (Russia foreign minister): Lavrov accused Ukraine of being behind the shooting and said it was “designed to sabotage” peace talks. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1971536/russias-deputy-spy-chief-in-serious-condition-after-attempt-on-life'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Kremlin (via Dmitry Peskov): The Kremlin said Putin was briefed, said he hoped Alekseyev would survive and recover, and pointed to heightened risks for senior military specialists during wartime. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1971536/russias-deputy-spy-chief-in-serious-condition-after-attempt-on-life'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Russia’s Investigative Committee: Investigators said an unidentified assailant shot Alekseyev multiple times in an apartment building and that authorities opened an investigation into the attack. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/a-deputy-chief-of-russian-military-intelligence-was-shot-and-wounded-in-moscow/article70599302.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/feb/06/russia-military-general-vladimir-alekseyev'>Russian general Vladimir Alekseyev in critical condition after Moscow shooting</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/a-deputy-chief-of-russian-military-intelligence-was-shot-and-wounded-in-moscow/article70599302.ece'>Deputy chief of Russian military intelligence was shot and wounded in Moscow</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1971536/russias-deputy-spy-chief-in-serious-condition-after-attempt-on-life'>Russia’s deputy spy chief in ‘serious condition’ after attempt on life</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c3686nzexp3o'>Russian general shot several times in Moscow</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/russian-intelligence-official-under-western-sanctions-is-shot-and-wounded-in-moscow1'>Russian intelligence official under Western sanctions is shot and wounded in Moscow</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/06/world/europe/russian-general-shot-moscow-alekseyev.html'>Russian General Is Shot in Latest Attack on a Top Military Leader in Moscow</a> - nytimes.com</li></ul>